hows, carnival, and, later, comedy television.Combining a chronological structure with groundbreaking research and a lively approach, Popular cinema in Brazil is the ideal introduction to Brazilian cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspectszBrazil. 0aMotion pictureszBrazilxHistory. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAmacio Mazzaropi.  aBrazil's socio-cultural landscape.  aBrazilian filmmaking.  aBrazilian popular cinema.  aTrapalhoes.  acarnivalesque inversions.  achanchada.  acinematic sub-genres.  aeconomic expansion.  alow-brow' cultural products.  apopular cinema.  apornochanchada.  apre-industrial traditions.  aradio.  atalking cinema.  awelfare system.1 aDennison, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShaw, Lisa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aShaw, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614172940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141729423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141729/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles